The paper deals with 3D semantic scene labeling using point clouds, which is a problem commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of an encoder-decoder architecture and message passing techniques suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The hierarchical graph framework and edge branch also suggest a focus on graph theory (cs.GR). Finally, the use of semantic labeling and contextual information suggests a focus on natural language processing (cs.CL).
